### Cost Katana OpenTelemetry: Baggage Propagation
### Propagate context across service boundaries

@baseUrl = https://cost-katana-backend.store/api
@apiKey = your_cost_katana_api_key
@gatewayUrl = https://cost-katana-backend.store/api/gateway

### 1. Basic Baggage Propagation
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
baggage: user_id=user123,tenant_id=tenant456,environment=production

{
  "model": "gpt-4",
  "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello with baggage"}]
}

###
# Baggage is automatically propagated to:
# - All downstream services
# - Logs and traces
# - Metrics and spans
# - Child requests

### 2. Multi-Value Baggage
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
baggage: user_id=user123,tenant_id=tenant456,team=engineering,project=ai-backend,cost_center=cc_789

{
  "model": "gpt-3.5-turbo",
  "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Request with multiple baggage items"}]
}

### 3. Baggage with Trace Context
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
traceparent: 00-4bf92f3577b34da6a3ce929d0e0e4736-00f067aa0ba902b7-01
baggage: request_id=req_abc123,correlation_id=corr_xyz789

{
  "model": "gpt-4",
  "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Request with trace and baggage"}]
}

###
# Use Cases:
